3. Creating GitHub Forks
========================
Forks are a useful tool for working with GitHub projects. Forks provide a way for any user to create their own personal copy of a GitHub repository which they can fully control without interfering with other users. They are widely used in managing open source projects. In this you will learn how to create a fork of a GitHub repository.


Creating GitHub Forks:
======================
1. Navigate to a particular repository using your browser ex: "https://github.com/linuxacademy/cicd-pipeline-train-schedule-git"
2. on top right there is button fork click on "Fork"  if popup come then select your account where you want to fork
3. now you can see your repo in your account.

